    • Constructor Detail

      • Sensor

        public Sensor(int i,
              java.lang.String t,
              int a,
              int o,
              int b,
              java.lang.String d,
              java.lang.String s,
              java.lang.String u,
              int st,
              java.lang.Double c)
        Creates a new Sensor
        Parameters:
        i - The ID of the sensor
        t - The tag of the sensor
        a - The address of the sensor (the CAN address it's being sent over)
        o - The byte offset from the address
        b - The byte length (number of bytes) of the sensor data
        d - The description of the sensor
        s - The system of the sensor
        u - The units of the sensor
        st - 1 for storage into the DB 0 for not
        c - The correction factor after the CAN read (decimals can't be sent over CAN so we must shift the value)
